# Skill Execution Rules

## Follow Skills Exactly

- When following a Skill workflow, execute steps in the documented order
- Do not skip steps unless the Skill explicitly marks them as optional
- Do not reorder steps
- Do not improvise or add steps that are not in the Skill

## Do Not Proceed Past Failures

- Do not proceed to the next step if the current step failed
- Report the failure to the user with the full error message
- Ask the user for next steps

## Collect All Prerequisites First

- Collect ALL required inputs from the user before starting any workflow
- Do not start a workflow with missing required inputs
- Optional inputs can use their documented defaults

## Sequential Processing

- When processing multiple test runs, complete Run 1 fully before starting Run 2
- Do not interleave steps from different test runs
- Each test run uses its own `test_run_id` and artifact directory

## Task Tracking

- Use task tracking for multi-step workflows to monitor progress
- Update task status as each step completes
- Mark the workflow as complete only when all steps have succeeded
